Male 
holotype
, morphology

: Total length (excluding chelicerae) 1.80. Colour in ethanol: opisthosoma, chelicera and legs brownish­yellow, pedipalps and carapace darker, reddish­brown. Carapace (
Fig. 3
) (0.67 x 0.66), granulated, with 102 setae, 6 on the anterior, 10 on the posterior margin. Tergal chaetotaxy: 12, 14, 12, 17, 18, 18, 18, 18, 18, 16, 9. Tergite XI without tactile setae. Sternal chaetotaxy: anterior sternite of genital region 24 setae; posterior sternite 14 setae; sternal formula (
IV­XI
) to 11: 14, 24, 24, 19, 16, 16, 15, 7. Coxal chaetotaxy (
Fig. 4a
) (left + right number of seta): pedipalpal coxa: 23+24; coxa I: 14+16; coxa II: 14+15; coxa III: 20+20; coxa IV: 29+28.
